The weekend is finally here, and with the current cold temperatures, you might probably choose to stay indoors and enjoy a cocktail with some Netflix. Here is how you can make a simple tasty cocktail for yourself, your loved one, or your friends. Gin can is best mixed with straight flavours like in Gin and Tonic. Ingredients: Blueberry Simple Syrup Blueberry Gin Cocktail Preparation Step 1 To make the Blueberry Simple Syrup, first in a small saucepan, add the blueberries, water, and granular sugar. While stirring, heat until the sugar dissolves and the mixture comes to a boil. Step 2 Remove from heat, then cover with a lid, allowing the mixture to reduce to room temperature. Step 3 Once it cools pour the Blueberry Simple Syrup over a mesh strainer and into a glass container to remove the blueberry pulp. Step 4 To make the cocktail, add ice cubes to a glass then add the blueberry syrup, gin and tonic water. Squeeze a fresh lemon and top off with blueberries. Stir until combined and enjoy. Cheers! Drink responsibly!